      • createSecurePassword

        public String createSecurePassword()
        Create a secure (random) password using a secure random number generator and a set of (reasonable) characters.

        The default rules are used to generate the password. See createSecurePassword(Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer)

        Returns:
        a String containing the new password
        See Also:
        createSecurePassword(Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer, Integer)

      • createSecurePassword

        public String createSecurePassword(Integer length,
                                   Integer minLowercaseLetters,
                                   Integer minUppercaseLetters,
                                   Integer minDigits,
                                   Integer minPunctuation,
                                   Integer minWhitespace)
        Create a secure (random) password using a secure random number generator, a set of (reasonable) characters, and meeting the specified rules.

        If any rule is null, it's default value will be used:

        • length: 18
        • minimum lowercase letters (a-z): 1
        • minimum uppercase letters (A-Z): 1
        • minimum digits (0-9): 1
        • minimum punctuation (?.!$%^*()-_+=~): 1
        • minimum whitespace ( ): 0
        Parameters:
        length - the required length of the generated password
        minLowercaseLetters - the required minimum number of lowercase letters
        minUppercaseLetters - the required minimum number of uppercase letters
        minDigits - the required minimum number of digits
        minPunctuation - the required minimum number of punctuation characters
        minWhitespace - the required minimum number of space characters
        Returns:
        a String containing the new password
